Integration test suite for `ctx-scan`, exercising `summarize`, `check_run`, and `update_run` against both an in-memory fake filesystem and a real tmpdir-backed `StdFs`. Together with `ctx-summarize`'s trait definitions this pins the observable contracts of the scan/hash/update pipeline; changing return shapes of `check_run`/`update_run`/`summarize` or the `.ctxignore`/`.gitignore` seeding behavior will break these tests.

Two in-memory fakes drive the hermetic half: `FakeFs` (a `BTreeMap<String,String>`-backed `Fs` impl with `with_source()` and `prompts_only()` constructors) and `RecordingAgent` (an `Agent` that returns `SUMMARY[{system}]` and records every `(system, user)` call pair for call-count assertions). `seed_prompts` pre-populates the two embedded prompt paths (`prompts/summarizer-leaf.md`, `prompts/summarizer-rollup.md`) that `runner::load_prompts` expects.

Key non-obvious behaviors asserted here, load-bearing for anyone touching the runner/walker:
- `.ctxignore` seeding from `.gitignore` happens **once**, on first contact; subsequent `.gitignore` edits are inert (`walk_seeds_ctxignore_from_gitignore_once_then_decouples`).
- `target/` is excluded by a built-in default even with no ignore file present.
- Hash freshness and artifact-existence are checked independently: hashes can be clean while `.ctx` artifacts are missing (`check_cycle_stale_then_missing_artifacts_then_edit_propagates`, referencing "finding #11").
- Editing one leaf file triggers exactly leaf + immediate-dir-rollup + root-rollup agent calls (3), not a full re-summarize.
- `update_run` removes orphaned `.ctx` leaves when their source file is deleted, reporting them via `report.orphan_leaves`.
- The scope gate (`runner::MAX_TARGETS`) refuses large unapproved runs with `SummError::ScopeTooLarge`, bypassable via an explicit approval flag.

`prompts_path()` resolves prompts via `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` rather than cwd, since production code loads them relative to cwd but tests need a cwd-independent path.